issues.suggested_fix:
Wrap the File in ManuallyDrop to prevent the drop:
```rust
use std::mem::ManuallyDrop;
let file = ManuallyDrop::new(unsafe { File::from_raw_fd(fd) });
let file_ref: &File = &*file;
let mut writer = BufWriter::new(file_ref); // &File: Write on Unix
```
Alternatively, change the API to accept `&mut dyn Write` so the caller manages fd lifetime entirely, eliminating the unsafe block.

Use the flat field layout directly:
```rust
let vertices = &mesh.vertices; // &Vec<f32>, flat [x0,y0,z0,...]
let triangles = &mesh.indices; // &Vec<u32>
// ...
for &idx in tri {
    let base = idx as usize * 3;
    writer.write_all(&mesh.vertices[base].to_le_bytes())?;
    writer.write_all(&mesh.vertices[base + 1].to_le_bytes())?;
    writer.write_all(&mesh.vertices[base + 2].to_le_bytes())?;
}
```
Note: vertices are already `f32` so the `as f32` cast in `v.x as f32` is also unnecessary.

Use `get` with an early error rather than direct indexing:
```rust
let base = idx as usize * 3;
let vx = *mesh.vertices.get(base).context("vertex index out of bounds")?;
```
